    <h2>This is inline Elements</h2>

    <span style="background-color: yellow;">Rohan Gadhave</span>

    <p>A block-level element always starts on a new line and takes up the full width available <br>
        An inline element does not start on a new line and it only takes up as much width as necessary <br>
        The <b>"div"</b> element is a block-level and is often used as a container for other HTML elements <br>
        The <b>"span"</b> element is an inline container used to mark up a part of a text, or a part of a document</p>

